The paper deals with the problem of forming coalitions among Cloud Providers (CPs) to reduce energy costs, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed algorithm is based on cooperative game theory (cs.GT) and the CPs' utility function is used to optimize their individual profit, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and control engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents numerical results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which is a topic related to computer engineering (cs.CE).
